   "body" : "Steps to reproduce:\r\n\r\n1. Start wallet with \"C:\\Program Files\\Bitcoin\\bitcoin-qt.exe\" -datadir=d:\\BitCoinData -Server \"\r\n2. Let it sync 100%\r\n3. Close wallet\r\n4. start again with \"-txindex\" flag added\r\n\r\nThe wallet re-sync, but at some point, the wallet just stop syncing, without any error message. When I\r\nclose the wallet (press the \"X\"), error appears \"Error: A fatal internal error occurred...\"\r\n\r\nAttached debug log\r\n[debug.log](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/files/1713674/debug.log)\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour\r\nWallet should sync, and I should be able to use \"getrawtransaction\" from debug console\r\n\r\nActual behaviour\r\nWallet stalls and then just crash when I close it\r\n\r\nScreenshots.\r\n![bitcoin_issue2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35986442/36065358-470923ba-0ea2-11e8-91f3-a258068a9426.jpg)\r\n![bitcoin_issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35986442/36065359-4729c44e-0ea2-11e8-85b8-a8f8551eb1f0.jpg)\r\n",
